{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 15 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:1",
      "text": "Now I would remind you, brethren, in what terms I preached to you the gospel, which you received, in which you stand,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:2",
      "text": "by which you are saved, if you hold it fast—unless you believed in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:3",
      "text": "For I delivered to you as of first importance what I also received, that Christ died for our sins in accordance with the scriptures,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:4",
      "text": "that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day in accordance with the scriptures,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:5",
      "text": "and that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:6",
      "text": "Then he appeared to more than five hundred brethren at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have fallen asleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:7",
      "text": "Then he appeared to James, then to all the apostles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:8",
      "text": "Last of all, as to one untimely born, he appeared also to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:9",
      "text": "For I am the least of the apostles, unfit to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:10",
      "text": "But by the grace of God I am what I am, and his grace toward me was not in vain. On the contrary, I worked harder than any of them, though it was not I, but the grace of God which is with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:11",
      "text": "Whether then it was I or they, so we preach and so you believed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:12",
      "text": "Now if Christ is preached as raised from the dead, how can some of you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:13",
      "text": "But if there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:14",
      "text": "if Christ has not been raised, then our preaching is in vain and your faith is in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:15",
      "text": "We are even found to be misrepresenting God, because we testified of God that he raised Christ, whom he did not raise if it is true that the dead are not raised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:16",
      "text": "For if the dead are not raised, then Christ has not been raised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:17",
      "text": "If Christ has not been raised, your faith is futile and you are still in your sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:18",
      "text": "Then those also who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:19",
      "text": "If for this life only we have hoped in Christ, we are of all men most to be pitied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:20",
      "text": "But in fact Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who have fallen asleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:21",
      "text": "For as by a man came death, by a man has come also the resurrection of the dead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:22",
      "text": "For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ shall all be made alive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:23",
      "text": "But each in his own order: Christ the first fruits, then at his coming those who belong to Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:24",
      "text": "Then comes the end, when he delivers the kingdom to God the Father after destroying every rule and every authority and power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:25",
      "text": "For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:26",
      "text": "The last enemy to be destroyed is death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:27",
      "text": "“For God has put all things in subjection under his feet.” But when it says, “All things are put in subjection under him,” it is plain that he is excepted who put all things under him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:28",
      "text": "When all things are subjected to him, then the Son himself will also be subjected to him who put all things under him, that God may be everything to every one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:29",
      "text": "Otherwise, what do people mean by being baptized on behalf of the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, why are people baptized on their behalf?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:30",
      "text": "Why am I in peril every hour?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:31",
      "text": "I protest, brethren, by my pride in you which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord, I die every day!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:32",
      "text": "What do I gain if, humanly speaking, I fought with beasts at Ephesus? If the dead are not raised, “Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:33",
      "text": "Do not be deceived: “Bad company ruins good morals.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:34",
      "text": "Come to your right mind, and sin no more. For some have no knowledge of God. I say this to your shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:35",
      "text": "But some one will ask, “How are the dead raised? With what kind of body do they come?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:36",
      "text": "You foolish man! What you sow does not come to life unless it dies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:37",
      "text": "And what you sow is not the body which is to be, but a bare kernel, perhaps of wheat or of some other grain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:38",
      "text": "But God gives it a body as he has chosen, and to each kind of seed its own body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:39",
      "text": "For not all flesh is alike, but there is one kind for men, another for animals, another for birds, and another for fish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:40",
      "text": "There are celestial bodies and there are terrestrial bodies; but the glory of the celestial is one, and the glory of the terrestrial is another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:41",
      "text": "There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for star differs from star in glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:42",
      "text": "So is it with the resurrection of the dead. What is sown is perishable, what is raised is imperishable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:43",
      "text": "It is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness, it is raised in power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:44",
      "text": "It is sown a physical body, it is raised a spiritual body. If there is a physical body, there is also a spiritual body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:45",
      "text": "Thus it is written, “The first man Adam became a living being”; the last Adam became a life-giving spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:46",
      "text": "But it is not the spiritual which is first but the physical, and then the spiritual.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:47",
      "text": "The first man was from the earth, a man of dust; the second man is from heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:48",
      "text": "As was the man of dust, so are those who are of the dust; and as is the man of heaven, so are those who are of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:49",
      "text": "Just as we have borne the image of the man of dust, we shall also bear the image of the man of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:50",
      "text": "I tell you this, brethren: flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God, nor does the perishable inherit the imperishable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:51",
      "text": "Lo! I tell you a mystery. We shall not all sleep, but we shall all be changed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.52",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:52",
      "text": "in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised imperishable, and we shall be changed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.53",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:53",
      "text": "For this perishable nature must put on the imperishable, and this mortal nature must put on immortality.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.54",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:54",
      "text": "When the perishable puts on the imperishable, and the mortal puts on immortality, then shall come to pass the saying that is written: “Death is swallowed up in victory.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.55",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:55",
      "text": "“O death, where is thy victory? O death, where is thy sting?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.56",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:56",
      "text": "The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.57",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:57",
      "text": "But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.15.58",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 15:58",
      "text": "Therefore, my beloved brethren, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that in the Lord your labor is not in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
